HEADWORD: Scotchman
<hw>Scotch"man</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Scotchmen</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A native or
inhabitant of Scotland; a Scot; a Scotsman.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>A piece of wood or stiff hide
placed over shrouds and other rigging to prevent chafe by the running
gear.</def> <rj><au>Ham. Nav. Encyc.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scotch rite</ent>⟦br⟧
